{
  "nodes": [
    {"id":"src","type":"text","x":-200,"y":-120,"width":300,"height":120,"color":"6","text":"## 1. Watchlist (Sources)\nThe channels you track (e.g. Eric Nowoslawski, Aaron Shepherd). Saved in Settings, table `Source`."},
    {"id":"profile","type":"text","x":-200,"y":420,"width":300,"height":150,"color":"6","text":"## Creator Profile (Settings)\nniche · offer/CTA · n_per_week · target_score · duration.\nFeeds *guidance* into generation. Single saved row."},

    {"id":"scrape","type":"text","x":260,"y":-120,"width":320,"height":190,"color":"2","text":"## 2. Scrape  ⟵ only when refresh=True\n**yt-dlp today / Apify proposed.**\nViews, likes, duration, title, description + top comments. No media download.\n\n⚠️ Runs ONLY for the *weekly batch*. The *on-command* generate skips this (refresh=false)."},

    {"id":"brain","type":"text","x":720,"y":-160,"width":320,"height":210,"color":"4","text":"## 3. THE BRAIN — brain.db (SQLite)\n• Videos + Comments (the data lake)\n• Channel baselines (median views)\n• **Virality model** (sklearn, ROC-AUC ~0.93) = the numeric GATE\n• Outliers / trending / velocity"},
    {"id":"wiki","type":"text","x":720,"y":300,"width":320,"height":140,"color":"4","text":"## Brain Wiki (markdown, flag OFF)\nKarpathy LLM-Wiki: styles, formats, pain-points that *compound*. Falls back to DB insight tables when off."},
    {"id":"mine","type":"text","x":720,"y":490,"width":320,"height":120,"color":"2","text":"## Mine (Claude)\nProven formats + audience pain-points.\n(Currently EMPTY — needs a click of the Dashboard \"Mine\" buttons.)"},

    {"id":"ctx","type":"text","x":1180,"y":-120,"width":320,"height":230,"color":"5","text":"## 4. _build_context()  ← THE KEY STEP\nAssembles the generation prompt **FROM THE BRAIN**, not from any single scraped video:\n• TRENDING NOW\n• PROVEN TOPICS (outlier titles)\n• CREATOR STYLE card\n• PROVEN FORMATS\n• AUDIENCE PAIN-POINTS\n• matching transcript excerpts"},

    {"id":"learn","type":"text","x":1180,"y":420,"width":320,"height":160,"color":"1","text":"## Learning context (the Claude-driven \"RL\")\nRecent DECLINES (+ your reasons) + what actually PERFORMED when published. Injected into every new generation."},

    {"id":"craft","type":"text","x":1640,"y":-120,"width":300,"height":180,"color":"5","text":"## 5. refine.craft()\nresearch → score with virality model → if weak, re-research a stronger angle → LOOP until score ≥ target_score (max 4 tries)."},

    {"id":"script","type":"text","x":1640,"y":300,"width":300,"height":150,"color":"5","text":"## 6. Write the package\nscript.generate_script() → description + booking CTA → thumbnail prompt.\nAll grounded in the same Brain context."},

    {"id":"queue","type":"text","x":2080,"y":-120,"width":300,"height":140,"color":"3","text":"## 7. ContentItem → QUEUE / Calendar\nidea · title · full script · description · thumbnail prompt · predicted score · nearest proven analogs. Status: proposed."},

    {"id":"review","type":"text","x":2080,"y":120,"width":300,"height":160,"color":"3","text":"## 8. Review\n✅ Approve / Schedule\n❌ Decline + reason → regenerate a better one\n📤 Mark published"},

    {"id":"reward","type":"text","x":2080,"y":360,"width":300,"height":150,"color":"1","text":"## 9. Reward loop\nPublished → scrape the REAL video → actual outlier multiplier → reward → back into Learning context."}
  ],
